items.title: Awesome Robotic Tooling
items.content_text:
### Development Environment / Version Control

*   [gitfs (⭐2.5k)](https://github.com/Presslabs/gitfs) - You can mount a remote repository's branch locally, and any subsequent changes made to the files will be automatically committed to the remote.
*   [git-sweep (⭐2.6k)](https://github.com/arc90/git-sweep) - A command-line tool that helps you clean up Git branches that have been merged into master.
items.content_html:

items.title: Awesome Dev Fun
items.content_text:
### Golang

*   [codeometer (⭐8)](https://github.com/rafael-santiago/codeometer) - It measures your code in real world units of measurement also comparing the evaluated distance to famous places and monuments. Codeometer supports plain code files, zipped files and remote git repos. Doing all stuff as a straightforward command line tool or as a web tool through its embedded httpd (tls supported).
items.content_html:
Golang

  • codeometer (⭐8) - It measures your code in real world units of measurement also comparing the evaluated distance to famous places and monuments. Codeometer supports plain code files, zipped files and remote git repos. Doing all stuff as a straightforward command line tool or as a web tool through its embedded httpd (tls supported).

items.title: Awesome Dotnet Core
items.content_text:
### Frameworks, Libraries and Tools / Application Templates

*   [CleanArchitecture (⭐17k)](https://github.com/ardalis/CleanArchitecture) - A starting point for Clean Architecture with ASP.NET Core. Clean Architecture is just the latest in a series of names for the same loosely-coupled, dependency-inverted architecture. You will also find it named hexagonal, ports-and-adapters, or onion architecture.
*   [CleanArchitecture (SPA) (⭐18k)](https://github.com/JasonGT/CleanArchitecture) - Solution template for creating a Single Page App (SPA) with Angular 8 and ASP.NET Core 3 following the principles of Clean Architecture
items.content_html:

items.content_text:
